Subject: [PATCH 4/6] ia64: add SN2 hooks to core ia64 code

Targeted #ifdef CONFIG_IA64_SGI_SN2 modifications to existing ia64 files.

  - io.h: SN2 I/O overrides (inb/outb/readl/writel route through SHUB)
  - mmiowb.h: SN2 custom MMIO write barrier
  - hw_irq.h: SN2 IRQ vector definitions
  - setup.c: sn_setup()/sn_cpu_init() calls, early console
  - acpi.c: SN2 ACPI/NUMA node mapping via SAL
  - msi_ia64.c: MSI delegation to SN2
  - irq_ia64.c, smpboot.c, sal.c: SN2 hooks
  - uncached.c: SN2 cache flush
  - mm/init.c: #ifdef guard for arch_sync_dma_for_cpu (5.5 API fix)
  - mm/tlb.c: SN2 TLB purge
  - pci/pci.c: SN2 PCI bus fixup

---

--- a/arch/ia64/include/asm/hw_irq.h	2026-03-08 02:38:22.000000000 +0000
+++ b/arch/ia64/include/asm/hw_irq.h	2026-03-08 04:03:38.244480710 +0000
@@ -153,7 +153,11 @@
 static inline ia64_vector
 irq_to_vector (int irq)
 {
+#ifdef CONFIG_IA64_SGI_SN2
+	return (ia64_vector)irq;
+#else
 	return irq_cfg[irq].vector;
+#endif
 }
 
